{
  "texts": [
    "It performs better classification even with sparse data and is unaffected by the vanishing gradient problem.",
    "The Moderate Demented class has poor classification performance.",
    "Sadat et al. (2021) implemented five state-of-the-art CNN models viz., ResNet152V2, Inception-ResNetV2 (Szegedy et al. 2017), VGG19, EfficientNetB5 (Tan and Le 2019), EfficientNetB6, and a custom-designed model.",
    "Ensemble learning is employed by combining various combinations of the six models to improve the overall outcome.",
    "This approach achieves an accuracy of 96%."
  ]
}